- They called me.

239
00:20:09,459 --> 00:20:11,753
- I know this cop, man.
- Yeah?

240
00:20:11,878 --> 00:20:15,298
Maybe we should help him out.
Tell him who did what.

241
00:20:15,382 --> 00:20:18,259
Stop wilding, Kimmy. I said I got this.

242
00:20:18,676 --> 00:20:21,638
Tosha's people wanna know what happened.

243
00:20:21,721 --> 00:20:26,309
Say she caught one taking them boys down.
Ain't no need to involve the police.

244
00:20:26,851 --> 00:20:30,730
- Sound to me like he involved already.
- I told you, I got this.

245
00:20:45,328 --> 00:20:49,249
My husband worked for Mr. Cooper
at the American can.

246
00:20:49,332 --> 00:20:53,586
He made good money.
We saved up and bought this house.

247
00:20:54,337 --> 00:20:57,799
There were white families still living
in the neighborhood then.

248
00:20:57,882 --> 00:21:00,677
The neighborhood has changed.

249
00:21:00,927 --> 00:21:04,931
- This is a picture of the house.
- Oh.

250
00:21:08,852 --> 00:21:12,105
City-owned, taxes paid and all.

251
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:14,023
It is very nice.

252
00:21:16,067 --> 00:21:19,487
- But I can't afford that.
- You don't have to worry.

253
00:21:19,612 --> 00:21:23,616
It's all taken care of.
It's a special program we have.

254
00:21:23,700 --> 00:21:30,457
It's for people who are living in
really bad situations, you know,

255
00:21:30,623 --> 00:21:33,084
with the drug trafficking outside.

256
00:21:34,043 --> 00:21:38,256
- And this is a good neighborhood.
- Mm-hm.

257
00:21:38,381 --> 00:21:45,054
It's safe and it's on the number 19 line
and it's walking distance from your church.

258
00:21:46,055 --> 00:21:50,226
Officer, this is the only home I know.

259
00:21:50,560 --> 00:21:52,395
It's all I've got.

260
00:21:52,479 --> 00:21:56,983
Now, you say you have a program
that can place me somewhere else

261
00:21:57,066 --> 00:22:00,320
but you ain't got no program
for what's outside my door?

262
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:15,752
You weren't lying.

263
00:22:17,504 --> 00:22:21,674
Yeah. I told you. And I've been
all over these blocks like you said.

264
00:22:21,925 --> 00:22:25,178
I haven't seen any cameras, nobody peekin'.

265
00:22:25,553 --> 00:22:29,599
Monk man has been here for days
and narcos haven't even blinked.

266
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:32,519
I'll tell you what.

267
00:22:32,727 --> 00:22:36,272
Put some of my people on it.
Just them young 'uns.

268
00:22:36,397 --> 00:22:39,943
Make the package real small,
just in case this a trap.

269
00:22:40,068 --> 00:22:43,947
- I wanna hear directly from you on this.
- I'm on it.

270
00:22:45,782 --> 00:22:48,076
This shit is just bugged out.

271
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:59,170
String called, said to tell you
he's gonna be late.

272
00:23:05,301 --> 00:23:09,305
- Are you telling me we're weak?
- I reached out to black Donnie.

273
00:23:10,014 --> 00:23:13,601
Ok, spit it out. Stop
fuckin' double-talkin' me.

274
00:23:14,644 --> 00:23:19,816
Black Donnie ain't having any of it. Says
brother mouzone put a hex on all of us.

275
00:23:20,775 --> 00:23:21,943
What about peacock?

276
00:23:22,026 --> 00:23:24,821
Peacock hired out with some Dominicans.

277
00:23:25,697 --> 00:23:27,115
What about eggy mule?

278
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:30,702
Eggy locked up.
Caught a nickel with the feds for a pistol.

279
00:23:31,661 --> 00:23:33,413
What about shorty Boyd?

280
00:23:34,497 --> 00:23:37,875
Shorty Boyd went
and cleaned his whole act up.

281
00:23:39,252 --> 00:23:41,421
Yeah, I know. Fucked us all up.

282
00:23:42,505 --> 00:23:43,506
What we got?

283
00:23:44,966 --> 00:23:48,094
The soldier you sent at us, cutty,
he gonna work out,

284
00:23:48,177 --> 00:23:50,847
but the rest of them dudes, I don't know.

285
00:23:51,639 --> 00:23:55,685
Listen, big man,
you're about to earn your fucking keep.

286
00:23:55,768 --> 00:23:58,646
You get cutty and the best of the rest

287
00:23:58,730 --> 00:24:02,025
and you put a hurtin' on marlo.
I want my corners.

288
00:24:07,196 --> 00:24:09,032
What the fuck?

289
00:24:10,283 --> 00:24:12,035
- What now?
- Problems, Mr. Bell.

290
00:24:12,118 --> 00:24:14,787
This ain't the time for problems.
I got places to be.

291
00:24:14,871 --> 00:24:19,125
We're being told it may take weeks
to get these changes approved.

292
00:24:19,208 --> 00:24:21,628
- Weeks?
- Meanwhile you lose money.

293
00:24:21,711 --> 00:24:24,464
How does anybody make money in this game?

294
00:24:24,547 --> 00:24:28,259
Every time I think we're good,
you back in my pockets.

295
00:24:33,765 --> 00:24:36,726
- You need to make a call.
- Again?

296
00:24:36,893 --> 00:24:41,230
He's the consultant, right?
You're paying him to consult, right?

297
00:24:42,023 --> 00:24:45,109
This is why we hire
a politically connected guy.

298
00:24:45,276 --> 00:24:49,656
He goes downtown and does for us
what we can't do for ourselves.

299
00:24:50,406 --> 00:24:52,909
Democracy in action, Mr. Bell.

300
00:24:57,288 --> 00:25:00,541
All right, me and slim,
we're gonna work through the alleys

301
00:25:00,625 --> 00:25:02,502
and hit 'em from the sides.

302
00:25:02,585 --> 00:25:05,254
I want you to come through here.

303
00:25:06,506 --> 00:25:09,008
Slow down, through the intersection.

304
00:25:09,092 --> 00:25:14,514
Ohh. If we come up this way,
we ain't got to cross no intersection.

305
00:25:14,597 --> 00:25:19,102
Come that way? You puttin' your driver
in the line of fire, man.

306
00:25:19,268 --> 00:25:21,938
Think on it. He gettin' taken out.

307
00:25:22,271 --> 00:25:25,233
Car gonna crash. Where that put you at?

308
00:25:25,316 --> 00:25:28,444
You don't wanna be shootin'
across your driver.

309
00:25:29,654 --> 00:25:34,659
All right, come in easy.
We're gonna have their full attention.

310
00:25:34,784 --> 00:25:38,621
And pick your targets,
drop 'em and move out quick.

311
00:25:38,705 --> 00:25:40,540
- Who drivin'?
- I'm under the wheel.

312
00:25:40,623 --> 00:25:43,960
Slow down at the end and toss your weapons.

313
00:25:44,210 --> 00:25:49,382
Get rid of any shell casings that kick back
in the car. Police could trace them.

314
00:25:49,465 --> 00:25:52,301
- Toss the gloves, too?
- No, hold on to them.

315
00:25:52,427 --> 00:25:54,762
They're gonna have
that DNA shit all on 'em.

316
00:25:54,971 --> 00:25:57,849
It's gonna take us some time to get set up

317
00:25:57,932 --> 00:26:01,060
so we need y'all to lay back
four or five blocks.

318
00:26:01,144 --> 00:26:03,855
When we ready,
we're gonna get you on the burner.

319
00:26:03,938 --> 00:26:06,733
But y'all hold tight till
I call you. You got it?

320
00:26:06,816 --> 00:26:11,654
We can handle our end. You just make sure
there's some fuckin' work left for us.

321
00:26:11,738 --> 00:26:14,282
I don't wanna feel like some decoy.

322
00:26:14,449 --> 00:26:16,451
Damn right about that.

323
00:26:17,994 --> 00:26:20,538
It's just to relocate, no big deal.

324
00:26:20,621 --> 00:26:23,124
I'm not asking for
round-the-clock protection.

325
00:26:23,499 --> 00:26:27,545
No big deal? Where the fuck
am I gonna find a house for this old broad?

326
00:26:27,670 --> 00:26:31,090
I got one. It's a foreclosure
on the harford road.

327
00:26:31,174 --> 00:26:35,261
All you gotta do is file the petition.
My boys'll move her in.

328
00:26:37,138 --> 00:26:42,226
She's a witness against a violent drug
crew. Without her, it won't go fonnard.

329
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:46,939
She's 73 years old.
Brave old broad to be doing this, but...

330
00:26:47,023 --> 00:26:50,860
Come on, ray.
We just lost a witness in a drug case.

331
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:52,583
We don't wanna lose another one so quick.

332
00:26:57,533 --> 00:27:00,036
If rawls gets wind of this,
you forged my signature.

333
00:27:02,288 --> 00:27:05,541
- Where's she living now?
- Vincent street, sector two.

334
00:27:06,042 --> 00:27:09,504
- That's a bad location?
- You wouldn't believe it.

335
00:27:15,927 --> 00:27:19,013
Wait for the call. What
if they've got lookouts?

336
00:27:19,096 --> 00:27:22,308
If we wait, it'll be over
by the time we get there.

337
00:27:22,391 --> 00:27:25,686
Plus, how's that gonna play with avon, man?

338
00:27:26,354 --> 00:27:27,647
They takin' all the credit.

339
00:27:40,326 --> 00:27:41,661
Yo, fellas, strap up.

340
00:27:54,423 --> 00:27:57,969
There go that motherfucker nay-nay.
I say we take him.

341
00:27:58,052 --> 00:28:01,889
- We should wait for the call.
- We wait, he gonna get away.

342
00:28:05,893 --> 00:28:07,728
Go, go, go!

343
00:28:14,986 --> 00:28:16,487
Get out, get out!

344
00:28:34,380 --> 00:28:35,965
What the fuck?

345
00:28:42,430 --> 00:28:46,434
Didn't I say something
about waiting for a fuckin' phone call?

346
00:28:59,906 --> 00:29:03,117
You know how you blow off
half the invitations you get?

347
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:07,246
- Ribbon cuttings, playground clean-ups?
- No choice.

348
00:29:07,371 --> 00:29:10,374
I got one to a fundraiser
for the delta phis.

349
00:29:10,499 --> 00:29:12,460
I drag my ass over to the forum.

350
00:29:13,169 --> 00:29:16,339
Who was there in his ironsides
but odell Watkins.

351
00:29:16,464 --> 00:29:17,757
The rainmaker.

352
00:29:17,840 --> 00:29:22,053
Talking in public
about being disappointed in the mayor.

353
00:29:23,429 --> 00:29:29,018
- Disappointed. Yeah? Like how?
- Like sincerely disappointed.

354
00:29:29,685 --> 00:29:32,925
The way you'd be with one of your kids.
He really wanted to see the mayor pressed.

355
00:29:34,398 --> 00:29:38,361
Maybe somebody can take
a run at Royce in next year's primary.

356
00:29:38,444 --> 00:29:41,113
Like who? Madam council president?

357
00:29:42,239 --> 00:29:47,703
- Mickey pepper would give him a fight.
- No, Mick won't risk it.

358
00:29:47,912 --> 00:29:50,456
Well, you gotta have someone with balls.

359
00:29:50,539 --> 00:29:52,208
And somebody black.

360
00:29:53,292 --> 00:29:55,544
This being Baltimore an' all.

361
00:30:01,884 --> 00:30:04,303
- How many y'all take?
- Two.

362
00:30:05,471 --> 00:30:08,683
Didn't get nearly a shot off.

363
00:30:08,766 --> 00:30:10,851
That speaks to the quality
of barksdale people.

364
00:30:11,060 --> 00:30:14,689
He's gonna come back at you.
It ain't gonna stop at this.

365
00:30:15,106 --> 00:30:16,607
I don't want it to stop.

366
00:30:16,816 --> 00:30:18,818
Barksdale weak today.

367
00:30:21,237 --> 00:30:26,075
- And he ain't working with my ammunition.
- No doubt you carryin' a full clip.

368
00:30:26,325 --> 00:30:29,161
But when you're at the head of the table,

369
00:30:29,245 --> 00:30:32,206
once you there, you've got to hold it down.

370
00:30:34,125 --> 00:30:35,835
Sound like one of them good problems.

371
00:30:37,003 --> 00:30:42,591
Yeah. Prison and graveyards,
full of boys who wore the crown.

372
00:30:42,675 --> 00:30:45,803
But they wore it. It's
my turn to wear it now.

373
00:30:49,181 --> 00:30:53,686
- We're gonna do this, right, Chris?
- It's ready like yesterday, dawg.

374
00:30:55,563 --> 00:30:57,148
Want a white t, man?

375
00:30:57,273 --> 00:30:59,775
Need to get yourself a white t, dawg.

376
00:31:02,695 --> 00:31:04,613
So you working your plan, bubs?

377
00:31:04,697 --> 00:31:08,701
- Dollar here, dollar there, kima.
- So why did you call?

378
00:31:09,660 --> 00:31:12,705
Are you still interested
in that boy, marlo?

379
00:31:16,125 --> 00:31:20,254
You wanna keep getting paid,
you need to get your ass up to park heights

380
00:31:20,337 --> 00:31:22,298
where kintel got them corners.

381
00:31:22,923 --> 00:31:24,550
Kintel?

382
00:31:24,675 --> 00:31:28,512
My bosses don't give a fuck about marlo.
Stringer neither.

383
00:31:28,763 --> 00:31:32,933
That's too bad because now
we've got a whole lot of drama.

384
00:31:33,017 --> 00:31:35,853
- What happened?
- That young buck marlo,

385
00:31:36,187 --> 00:31:40,149
he just dropped two of barksdale's soldiers
two hours past.

386
00:31:40,316 --> 00:31:43,444
- What?
- Them corners is all jumpin' bad.

387
00:31:43,527 --> 00:31:46,072
I thought marlo had
the corners with stringer.

388
00:31:46,155 --> 00:31:49,992
All I know is Mario
is flyin' his own colors.

389
00:31:50,076 --> 00:31:52,495
West Side's about to be all Baghdad.

390
00:31:53,996 --> 00:31:56,582
But y'all looking for whatshisname, kintel.

391
00:31:56,707 --> 00:31:59,668
Y'all are too fickle with
bubs, man. I swear.

392
00:32:01,003 --> 00:32:04,215
A little gift for you
and your boys. Call me.

393
00:32:05,508 --> 00:32:07,593
Whitey sale! Whitey sale!

394
00:32:09,053 --> 00:32:12,181
Deputy, I am aware of the incident
and my men are on it.

395
00:32:12,348 --> 00:32:16,310
We called in the flex squad
and my deu is out canvassing.

396
00:32:16,560 --> 00:32:17,978
And what do we know?

397
00:32:18,854 --> 00:32:22,525
It seems to be rival gangs.
What does homicide have?

398
00:32:22,608 --> 00:32:25,778
Fuck homicide. I'm asking you for answers.

399
00:32:26,195 --> 00:32:28,572
- Sir, my men...
- And you have none.

400
00:32:28,697 --> 00:32:30,699
My men are out there...

401
00:32:35,704 --> 00:32:39,208
- What do we know that we can tell the man?
- Rival gangs.

402
00:32:39,375 --> 00:32:40,709
Which gangs?

403
00:32:41,085 --> 00:32:43,879
Gangs. Assholes who don't like each other.

404
00:32:49,635 --> 00:32:52,763
I'm sorry, major, but we got nothing on it.

405
00:33:03,607 --> 00:33:08,154
Play it. It don't make me no never mind.
It's all about trumps.

406
00:33:13,284 --> 00:33:14,660
Evening, Omar.

407
00:33:16,871 --> 00:33:18,873
Evening, bruiser.

408
00:33:23,711 --> 00:33:26,547
Speaking of them trumps now.

409
00:33:33,095 --> 00:33:35,014
Hey, everybody.

410
00:33:36,932 --> 00:33:39,268
What's for dinner, Jen? I'm starving.

411
00:33:39,393 --> 00:33:40,936
It's working.

412
00:33:45,774 --> 00:33:48,777
- Hi, daddy.
- How are you doing, beautiful?

413
00:33:49,069 --> 00:33:50,946
Daddy, we shared with you.

414
00:33:52,072 --> 00:33:55,284
That's nice.
Have you seen that tape I was watching?

415
00:33:55,367 --> 00:33:57,453
I don't know what you're talking about.

416
00:33:57,578 --> 00:34:01,582
The videotape from last Monday night's
council meeting.

417
00:34:01,665 --> 00:34:06,837
Keiffer tried to block my resolution but
I laid him out good. I was in rare form.

418
00:34:06,921 --> 00:34:09,924
- You seen it?
- Maybe you left it in the VCR?

419
00:34:12,885 --> 00:34:15,304
What? Son of a bitch!

420
00:34:17,681 --> 00:34:20,851
- Who the hell...?
- Franky shared his sandwich with you.

421
00:34:21,310 --> 00:34:25,481
We hid it so no one else could eat it
before you came home.

422
00:34:33,489 --> 00:34:35,369
Can I get some chips
and pickles with that, too?

423
00:34:39,745 --> 00:34:45,292
I don't wanna disrespect you.
String been good to me, you know?

424
00:34:46,001 --> 00:34:49,672
Not just my bills. Him and avon
probably think they owe me that much.

425
00:34:49,755 --> 00:34:51,048
Mmm-hmm.

426
00:34:51,423 --> 00:34:55,844
- And it ain't what people might be saying.
- What they saying?

427
00:34:56,053 --> 00:34:57,930
It ain't like I don't miss Dee.

428
00:34:59,098 --> 00:35:00,724
I do.

429
00:35:01,267 --> 00:35:05,104
Yeah, well, I miss him, too.

430
00:35:05,187 --> 00:35:08,774
- But he's been gone a while now.
- More than a year.

431
00:35:10,818 --> 00:35:12,528
Stringer's fine.

432
00:35:13,279 --> 00:35:15,114
No denying that.

433
00:35:17,199 --> 00:35:19,034
I feel safe around him.

434
00:35:21,704 --> 00:35:26,834
You asking to get with string,
I'm ok with that.

435
00:35:28,168 --> 00:35:31,255
- I thought you was gonna be mad.
- Uh-uh.

436
00:35:33,299 --> 00:35:36,969
I mean, everything with Dee
is so messed up, you know?

437
00:35:37,052 --> 00:35:39,305
I mean, every time I think about it...

438
00:35:40,222 --> 00:35:42,224
And you know this one police,

439
00:35:42,349 --> 00:35:45,602
he came by here and
brought it all up again.

440
00:35:45,686 --> 00:35:49,023
- Who did?
- Police detective from the city.

441
00:35:49,148 --> 00:35:53,402
The one that tried to turn Dee on avon
when he got pulled up in Jersey.

442
00:35:53,527 --> 00:35:54,862
White boy?

443
00:35:54,945 --> 00:35:56,864
- Bushy hair?
- Yeah.

444
00:35:57,865 --> 00:35:59,575
What did he say?

445
00:36:01,076 --> 00:36:02,745
What did he say?

446
00:36:03,579 --> 00:36:08,292
He said maybe d'Angelo didn't take...

447
00:36:09,668 --> 00:36:11,128
You know.

448
00:36:11,295 --> 00:36:13,547
Take his own life.

449
00:36:13,922 --> 00:36:16,258
He said maybe it was somethin' else.

450
00:36:17,926 --> 00:36:19,970
And he came to you with that?

451
00:36:20,095 --> 00:36:22,181
Left his card here one day

452
00:36:22,264 --> 00:36:24,350
but I didn't say nothing to the man.

453
00:36:24,433 --> 00:36:26,435
Just told stringer, is all.

454
00:36:27,561 --> 00:36:28,604
Hmm.

455
00:36:33,817 --> 00:36:36,153
She's gonna run for council?

456
00:36:36,278 --> 00:36:38,238
She is.

457
00:36:38,322 --> 00:36:40,991
Probably win, too, if I know her.

458
00:36:41,867 --> 00:36:44,119
And you're the proud husband?

459
00:36:49,958 --> 00:36:52,336
Not sure how that makes me feel.

460
00:36:53,462 --> 00:36:56,840
It's just for show until
the election next year.

461
00:36:58,050 --> 00:37:00,803
A city police lieutenant looks good
on her arm.

462
00:37:01,512 --> 00:37:03,514
Who even cares anymore?

463
00:37:03,597 --> 00:37:07,393
Everyone's either separated
or divorcing for the second time.

464
00:37:07,476 --> 00:37:09,770
This is a favor. For her.

465
00:37:11,313 --> 00:37:13,482
It's hard to explain.

466
00:37:23,492 --> 00:37:25,744
Look, I disappointed her.

467
00:37:27,496 --> 00:37:33,168
For years she told herself I was tracked
for deputy commissioner at worst,

468
00:37:33,252 --> 00:37:36,422
and past the police department, who knows?

469
00:37:36,547 --> 00:37:39,716
And there were some things
that happened a long time ago.

470
00:37:42,052 --> 00:37:43,720
I guess she wanted more out of me.

471
00:37:44,680 --> 00:37:47,891
And after a lot of
years and a lot of plans,

472
00:37:48,183 --> 00:37:52,229
it turns out I have a better head
for police work than climbing the ladder.

473
00:37:52,354 --> 00:37:56,400
She hung in there
